<p itemprop="description">A performance analyst measures, monitors, and analyses organisational performance using data and metrics. They create performance frameworks, develop KPIs, and provide insights to support performance improvement and strategic decision-making.</p>

<section class="role-details">
    <h2>Typical responsibilities</h2>
    <ul>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Develop and maintain performance measurement frameworks and KPIs</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Analyse performance data to identify trends, patterns, and improvement opportunities</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Create performance dashboards and reports for stakeholders</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Support performance reviews and strategic planning processes</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Collaborate with business units to define performance metrics</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Provide analytical support for performance improvement initiatives</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Monitor and report on service delivery and operational performance</li>
    </ul>
</section>

